      <h2><a href="index.html">Crystal by Example</a>: Hello World</h2>
      
      <table>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>Our first program will print the classic &quot;Hello, World!&quot; message.
Here's the full source code.</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code">
           <div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="nb">puts</span> <span class="s2">&quot;Hello, World!&quot;</span>
</pre></div>

          </td>
        </tr>
        
      </table>
      
      <table>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>To run the program, put the code in <code>hello-world.cr</code> and use the <code>crystal</code> command.</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code leading">
           <div class="highlight"><pre><span></span>$ crystal hello-world.cr
Hello, World!
</pre></div>

          </td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>Once you're done changing your program, you'll want to compile it to a binary. That's what the <code>crystal build</code> command is for.</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code leading">
           <div class="highlight"><pre><span></span>$ crystal build hello-world.cr
$ ls
hello-world     hello-world.cr
</pre></div>

          </td>
        </tr>
        
        <tr>
          <td class="docs">
            <p>We can then execute the binary directly</p>

          </td>
          <td class="code">
           <div class="highlight"><pre><span></span>$ ./hello-world
Hello, World!
</pre></div>

          </td>
        </tr>
        
      </table>
      
